Class Meeting

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.java.com.hexcore.vrmeeting_hostserver.ServerComponent
      • main.java.com.hexcore.vrmeeting_hostserver.meeting.Meeting
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MessageBroadcastSubscriber

    public class Meeting
extends ServerComponent
implements MessageBroadcastSubscriber
    Represents a collection of Users who can communicate between one another A meeting has an ID, a number of people present and 1 presenter Once started a meeting will execute events added to a queue by the connections present in the meeting clients
    Author:
    Psymj1 (Marcus)

    • Method Detail

      • addNewParticipant

        public void addNewParticipant(MeetingClient client)
                       throws UserExistsException
        Add a new participant to the meeting. Note this will not send out a notification to all other clients. This must be done by the client sending a JOIN message to the server Also adds the client to the sub components of the meeting
        Parameters:
        client - The client of the participant to add
        Throws:
        UserExistsException - If the user referred to by the MeetingClient has already exists in the meeting, this is a comparison between the underlying user objects

      • removeParticipant

        public void removeParticipant(MeetingClient client)
        Removes a participant from the meeting if it is participating. Note this will not send out a notification to all other clients. This must be done by the client sending a LEFT message to the server
        Parameters:
        client - The client to remove
